name: North Tripyramid

trails_config.description: One of the most technical routes in the Whites. Features the 'North Slide,' a massive, steep rock slab that requires high-traction footwear and confidence on steep granite.

generated_description:
The Experience

Standing at 4180 feet, North Tripyramid is a standout peak in New Hampshire. Known for its approachable and scenic terrain, it offers a quintessential hiking experience.

The Challenge

Hikers often choose the **Tripyramid Loop via North Slide**, a **11.0 mile** route gaining significant elevation. As part of the **NH48 4000-Footers**, it draws peak-baggers from across the region.

Peak Bagging Logic

**Peak Bagging Opportunity:** Consider connecting this hike with **Sabbaday Falls**, which is just 3.0 miles away. Linking these peaks is a popular way to maximize your day on the trail.
